        <abstract>
            <p>It is strange that Agassiz, who is for the "sanctity of species", should favour Pallas’s view of hybrid origin of domestic dog.</p>
            <p>CL has not meant to advocate successive creation of types but to question assumption that all mammals descended from single stock. Why should a Triassic reptile or bird not move towards mammalian form because an ancestral marsupial has appeared? Believes recent appearance of rodents and bats in Australia explains their lack of development.</p>
            <p>Can CD supply a reference on plant extinction on St Helena?</p>
            <p>Believes marsupials better adapted for surviving drought in Australia than higher mammals.</p>
            <p>Will not press argument about lack of development of mammalian forms on islands, but CD should note objection.</p>
            <p>Does CD’s belief in multiple origin of dogs affect faith in single primates in different regions?</p> 
<p>Does time lapse between putative independently descended mammalian forms mean first form will "keep down" later incipient one? Thus <hi rend="italic">Homo sapiens</hi> has prevented improvement of other anthropomorphs; bats and rodents on islands would prevent improvement of lower forms into mammalian.</p> 
        </abstract>
